<TITLE> Bangladesh to host South Africa in a three-ODI and two-Test series </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Dec 5 (bdnews24.com) - Bangladesh will host South Africa in a three-ODI and a two-Test series in February-March next year. South Africa are scheduled to arrive here on February 14 and leave here on March 15, according to an itinerary released by the Bangladesh Cricket Board Wednesday. South Africa will open their four-week tour of Bangladesh playing a three-day warm-up match (February 17-19) at Narayaganj Osmani Stadium before taking on Bangladesh in the first Test from February 22 to 26 at Sher-e-Bangla National Stadium (SBNS) in Mirpur. The second Test (Feb 29 to Mar 4) will be held at Bir Shrestha Shaheed Ruhul Amin Stadium in Chittagong, which will also host the lone one-day warm-up match on Mar 7 and the first ODI on Mar 9. The SBNS will host the last two ODIs on Mar 12 and 14. 
